<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-367] Multi-Rail Documentation</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-367</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Documentation to be provided for the Multi-Rail feature being worked in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7734&quot; title=&quot;LNet Multi-Rail Project&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7734&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7734&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is important to note that we currently have a section (15.3) in the manual titled &quot;Multi-Rail Configurations with LNet&quot;.  This is going to cause mass confusion with the new use of the &quot;multi-rail&quot; term.  The entire documentation needs to be inspected to make sure we clearly distinguish between the two concepts and name them appropriately and consistently throughout the documentation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
